title: Celebrate St. Patrick's Day in Manassas, VA

organizations.name: northern virginia firefighters emerald society pipe

text:
Manassas St. Patrick’s Day Parade 2017 © St. Patricks Day Parade By Rachel Cooper Updated January 10, 2017 . 
The City of Manassas, Virginia celebrates St. Patrick’s Day each year with a community parade featuring Irish dance groups, the Northern Virginia Firefighters Emerald Society Pipe and Drum, Washington Scottish Pipe and Drum, Fairfax County Sheriff’s Coalition Pipe and Drum, the Marine Corps Color Guard and other area groups and organizations.March 11, 2017, 11 a.m. Parade Route The parade begins at the intersection of Quarry Rd. and Prescott Ave. and proceeds south to Center Street, continuing on Center Street ending at West Street. The parade reviewing stand is located at the end of the parade route at West and Center Sts. See a map of the parade route Parking Parking is available at the City Municipal Parking lots located on Prince William Street (near train depot), Across from the Train Station (Near Osborn HS), City Hall and on Church Street.
